# Notion DB Registry

> Per-user file. Filled by `/setup-wizard connect-tools` when it creates/connects Notion DBs in the user's workspace.

## How Notion is wired

This system uses Notion as the **operational layer** (CRM, tasks, finance, habits). The vault (Obsidian) holds knowledge; Notion holds operations.

For Notion access, MCP servers are configured in `.mcp.json` and tool calls use the `mcp__notion__*` namespace.

If the user has multiple Notion workspaces (e.g. personal + organizational), each workspace gets its own MCP server (`notion`, `notion-orgname`, etc.). Tool prefixes change accordingly. **Never mix prefixes** — different MCPs see different content.

## Notion API syntax (quick ref)

```
# Search
notion-search: query "Name"

# Query DB
notion-database-query: database_id "UUID"

# Update page
notion-update-page: page_id "UUID" + properties

# Create page
notion-create-pages: parent database_id + properties
```

> Use `data_source_id` (collection://...), not `database_id`, for queries — this is required since Notion API 2025-09-03.

